For the original version of the band, see
Queensrche
.

Formed in 2012 after longtime vocalist
Geoff Tate
's dismissal from
Queensrche
. The original band continued with new vocalist
Todd La Torre
and Tate claimed the band name and released an album in 2013 while legal proceedings continued. An agreement was eventually reached in April 2014 that only the original version of the band will continue using the name Queensrche effective August 31, 2014. The band has
announced
that they will continue under the name "Operation: Mindcrime".

This version of Queensrche reunited three members of Geoff Tate's previous band, Myth.
